general_comment: It seems as there was an issue with your submission, as I think half of your project was cut-off. But just make sure you submit your full pdf report in the next one, as I'm sure that the last section will pass as well. Thanks.

rubric.description:
### Project Files and Project Description
There are no project files required for the capstone proposal. Students will be expected to submit all necessary files for their submission to be evaluated. The **Machine Learning Nanodegree** project files and descriptions are available on the [Udacity MLND project GitHub](https://github.com/udacity/machine-learning). Below are some pre-curated projects that students may consider working on:

- [Robot Motion Planning](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ZFCH6jS3A5At7_v5IUM5OpAXJYiutFuSIjTzV_E-vdE/pub)
- [Healthcare](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1WzurKKa9AX2DnOH7KiB38mvozdOSemfkGpex8hdTy8c/pub)
- [Computer Vision](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1y-XfjkPFgUQxFIQ9bBncUSjs4HOf5E-45FrLYNBsZb4/pub)
- [Education](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1vjerjRQnWs1kLbZagDYT6rNqiwAG23Yj45oUY88IAxI/pub)
- [Investment and Trading](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ycGeb1QYKATG6jvz74SAMqxrlek9Ed4RYrzWNhWS-0Q/pub)

### Grading
Refer to the [reviewer guidelines](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-bf9kIA8SMTYXqUzZsIyfMdZXJOwe8hv4rvLXqAYvz4/pub?embedded=true) and the [best practices document](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1l7kBsXt4muZe7ZP9FjyymIzXQ49EgHEHPycru1dlUA8/pub?embedded=true) for this project whenever necessary.  
A [project proposal template](https://github.com/udacity/machine-learning/blob/master/projects/capstone/capstone_proposal_template.md) is provided to students and should be given as a resource when needed.

Mark the submission as **Ungradeable** if, at minimum, the PDF proposal is not present.
